Place the chocolate, butter, eggs and sugar into a bowl and mix together well.Add the flour, baking powder, cherries and cherry juice and fold together until smooth.Grease two mugs with butter, then spoon the mixture into each until three-quarters full. Cover each with cling film, place in the microwave and cook on full power for 2 minutes. Remove the cling film and cook for a further 30 seconds, or until risen and cooked through.To serve, top with the reserved cherries and drizzle with the melted chocolate.